非要强行跟我打招呼
how parts of me are hanging.

45
00:01:39,323 --> 00:01:41,490
你不要岔开话题
You know what I meant.

46
00:01:41,492 --> 00:01:43,125
好吧
All right, fine.

47
00:01:43,127 --> 00:01:44,293
就算
Let's say that

48
00:01:44,295 --> 00:01:45,411
我们要请人来家里玩
we were to entertain people.

49
00:01:45,413 --> 00:01:47,379
你想怎么玩?
What type of gathering did you have in mind?

50
00:01:47,381 --> 00:01:48,664
聚餐吗? 那么 是吃午饭?
Huh? A meal? Lunch?

51
00:01:48,666 --> 00:01:49,582
早午饭? 还是晚饭?
Brunch? Dinner?

52
00:01:49,584 --> 00:01:50,833
或者一起喝下午茶? 是正式的那种吗? 嗯?
Afternoon tea? A formal tea? Hmm?

53
00:01:50,835 --> 00:01:53,302
还是你想开趴? 那你想开哪种趴?
Is it a party? And if so, what kind of party?

54
00:01:53,304 --> 00:01:55,087
是有鸡尾酒的聚会?
Is it a cocktail party?

55
00:01:55,089 --> 00:01:56,639
微波炉食品聚会餐?
A Tupperware party?

56
00:01:56,641 --> 00:01:59,808
对了... 还是说你想开一个惊喜派对?
Ooh, yeah... is it a surprise party?

57
00:01:59,810 --> 00:02:01,010
不过最好可别是
Oh, I hope it's not

58
00:02:01,012 --> 00:02:02,678
传说中的 "西海岸派对" 因为歌里说
a West Coast party, 'cause according to

59
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:06,315
西海岸的派对根本停不下来
the man on the radio, a West Coast party don't stop.

60
00:02:06,317 --> 00:02:08,234
我的锅 我不应该提这事 对不起
I'm sorry I mentioned it.

61
00:02:08,236 --> 00:02:09,852
别这么说啦 你负责提建议
Oh, don't be. You get your hopes up,

62
00:02:09,854 --> 00:02:12,488
我负责否决 这就是团队合作嘛
I knock them down. That's called teamwork.

63
00:02:21,866 --> 00:02:23,365
它在踢我
That's a kick.

64
00:02:23,367 --> 00:02:25,034
真的在踢我
That's an actual kick.

65
00:02:30,341 --> 00:02:32,708
你干什么呢?
What are you doing?

66
00:02:32,710 --> 00:02:34,843
我感觉宝宝在踢我
I felt a kick.

67
00:02:34,845 --> 00:02:37,880
你肚子里有个孩子
There's a baby in there.

68
00:02:37,882 --> 00:02:41,183
是嘛 原来我放肚子里了啊
Oh, yeah, that's where I put it.

69
00:02:41,185 --> 00:02:44,270
我是说 我知道你怀孕了
Oh, I mean, I know you're pregnant.

70
00:02:44,272 --> 00:02:45,521
但是...
I just...

71
00:02:45,523 --> 00:02:48,390
我从来没意识到 怀孕就是
never connected the idea of pregnancy

72
00:02:48,392 --> 00:02:51,977
你肚子里有个真的孩子了
and you actually having a baby.

73
00:02:51,979 --> 00:02:55,781
你真的是麻省理工毕业的?
Which MIT did you go to?

74
00:02:59,203 --> 00:03:02,488
天啊 我们还没准备好迎接这个孩子啊!
Oh, God, we are not ready to have an infant in this house!

75
00:03:02,490 --> 00:03:04,740
没有婴儿床 没有尿布
We don't have a crib, we don't have diapers.

76
00:03:04,742 --> 00:03:06,241
也没做婴儿防护措施
We're not baby-proofed.

77
00:03:06,243 --> 00:03:10,079
路上随便一个人都能到我们家来掀马桶盖!
Anyone can just walk in off the street and lift our toilet lids!

78
00:03:10,081 --> 00:03:12,498
Howie 我们有的是时间慢慢做准备呢
Howie, we have time to do all that stuff.

79
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:13,916
是嘛?
Do we?

80
00:03:13,918 --> 00:03:15,084
你看看你
Look at you.

81
00:03:15,086 --> 00:03:18,003
Willy Wonka马上就要把你推进榨汁间了
Willy Wonka would roll you to the juicing room.

82
00:03:15,086 --> 00:03:18,003
{\an8} "查理的巧克力工厂"电影中有专门榨果汁的房间

83
00:03:19,757 --> 00:03:22,391
现在我也想踢你了
The next person kicking you will be me.

84
00:03:22,393 --> 00:03:23,342
快睡吧
Good night.

85
00:03:29,817 --> 00:03:31,817
我们这附近有好学校么...?
Are we even in a good school...?

86
00:03:31,819 --> 00:03:33,018
嗷!
Ow!

87
00:03:34,105 --> 00:03:37,606
我警告过你了 不怪我
I warned you, and I did it.

88
00:03:41,912 --> 00:03:43,112
这都是什么?
What's all this?

89
00:03:43,114 --> 00:03:45,698
这些都是给你的签名会准备的材料...
Oh, everything we need for your autograph session...

90
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:47,333
你的海报 还有马克笔
head shots, markers. 

91
00:03:47,335 --> 00:03:49,034
Lenard 你准备的这么齐全是挺好的
Okay. Leonard, it's sweet you're excited about this,

92
00:03:49,036 --> 00:03:52,171
但是只要有一个人要我的签名 那就是奇迹了
but it'll be a miracle if one person asks for my autograph.

93
00:03:52,173 --> 00:03:53,339
你开什么玩笑?
Are you kidding?

94
00:03:53,341 --> 00:03:55,624
我曾经花了20刀买Theo Sassler的签名
I once paid $20 for Theo Sassler's signature.

95
00:03:55,626 --> 00:03:56,875
- 那是谁?  - 我也不知道
- Who's that?  - Oh, I don't even know.

96
00:03:56,877 --> 00:03:59,678
只是觉得他的名字挺好听的 Theo Sassler!
I just liked his name. Theo Sassler!

97
00:04:00,631 --> 00:04:02,514
来来来 给你看这个
Oh, and look at this.

98
00:04:02,516 --> 00:04:04,717
我还准备了找零神器
I even got a change maker.

99
00:04:08,472 --> 00:04:10,773
小美女 想换多少零钱啊?
How much change you want, little lady?

100
00:04:12,059 --> 00:04:15,394
讲真 我现在想换的可不只是零钱
Oh, there's so much I want to change.

101
00:04:15,396 --> 00:04:19,114
你要是想换1刀的硬币 尽管来找我
Yeah, well, if it's a dollar, you're in luck.

102
00:04:23,487 --> 00:04:25,821
这是什么情况?
What's going on here?

103
00:04:25,823 --> 00:04:28,540
你说你想邀请别人来家里做客
You expressed an interest in having people over,

104
00:04:28,542 --> 00:04:31,043
我觉得我反对的太快了
and I feel I dismissed it too quickly.

105
00:04:31,045 --> 00:04:32,411
所以 我亲自动手
So, I took matters

106
00:04:32,413 --> 00:04:35,164
准备了早午餐 还邀请了几个人过来
into my own hands, and I arranged a brunch.

107
00:04:35,166 --> 00:04:36,999
你太好了
Well, that's so nice.

108
00:04:37,001 --> 00:04:38,500
都有谁要来啊?
Who's coming?

109
00:04:38,502 --> 00:04:41,637
Stuart 地质实验室的Bert
Oh, uh, Stuart, Bert from the geology lab,

110
00:04:41,639 --> 00:04:43,972
还有楼下的Petrescu太太
and Mrs. Petrescu from downstairs.

111
00:04:43,974 --> 00:04:45,674
你是说住在二楼的那个罗马尼亚女士吗?
You mean the Romanian lady on the second floor?

112
00:04:45,676 --> 00:04:46,675
是的
Yes.

113
00:04:46,677 --> 00:04:48,010
有个有意思的事:
Oh, fun story:

114
00:04:48,012 --> 00:04:50,345
她是跟十个兄弟姐妹一起长大的
she grew up with ten siblings.

115
00:04:50,347 --> 00:04:53,098
也有可能是跟企鹅 她的英语简直穷凶极恶
Or possibly penguins. Her English is atrocious.

116
00:04:54,602 --> 00:04:56,151
这组合还挺怪的
That's an odd mix of people.

117
00:04:56,153 --> 00:04:58,020
这是我们第一次作为主人招待别人
Well, for our first time hosting,

118
00:04:58,022 --> 00:05:00,656
我觉得实施一次试验还挺明智的
I thought it would be wise to conduct a trial run.

119
00:05:00,658 --> 00:05:01,940
你知道的 就好像那次
You know, like how I practiced

120
00:05:01,942 --> 00:05:03,492
我去万圣节鬼屋之前
for that Halloween haunted house

121
00:05:03,494 --> 00:05:06,862
用公交车站的卫生间来做练习一样
by going into the bathroom at the bus station.

122
00:05:06,864 --> 00:05:09,248
但你后来也没去那个鬼屋啊
You never went into that haunted house.

123
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:11,500
你也没看见车站里跳出来吓我一跳的东西
You never saw what jumped out at me at the bus station.

124
00:05:11,502 --> 00:05:14,420
好吧 谢谢你 Sheldon
Well, thank you, Sheldon.

125
00:05:14,422 --> 00:05:16,455
这是个有趣的惊喜
This is a fun surprise.

126
00:05:16,457 --> 00:05:18,424
而真正的惊喜是
Oh. Well, the real surprise is

127
00:05:18,426 --> 00:05:21,009
你对于我擅长惊喜表示惊讶
how surprised you are that I'm great at surprises.

128
00:05:21,011 --> 00:05:22,961
可是那完全不是惊喜啊
Well, that's not a surprise at all.

129
00:05:22,963 --> 00:05:25,180
我是说 如果我知道你擅长惊喜的话
I mean, if I knew you were good at surprises,

130
00:05:25,182 --> 00:05:26,381
那我就会对这个惊喜有所预料
I would have expected the surprise,

131
00:05:26,383 --> 00:05:27,766
从而不为它而感到惊喜了
and therefore not have been surprised.

132
00:05:27,768 --> 00:05:29,051
但正是因为我得到了惊喜 所以我不知道你擅长惊喜
But as it is, I didn't know,

133
00:05:29,053 --> 00:05:32,187
所以我对此表示的惊讶就不应该让你感到惊讶
and therefore my surprise should be unsurprising.

134
00:05:32,189 --> 00:05:35,140
别让我变得这么欲火难耐 客人都要来了
Don't get me all randy. Guests are on the way.

135
00:05:39,313 --> 00:05:40,946
嗨
Hi.

136
00:05:40,948 --> 00:05:42,481
嘿 你们刚刚去哪儿啦?
Hey, where you been?

137
00:05:42,483 --> 00:05:44,817
哦 我们刚刚去为宝宝买了点东西
Oh, we went and did a little shopping for the baby.

138
00:05:44,819 --> 00:05:46,702
等你看到我们买到的婴儿床就知道了
Wait till you see the crib we found.

139
00:05:46,704 --> 00:05:48,821
你们没经过我就自己买了个婴儿床?
You bought a crib without me?

140
00:05:48,823 --> 00:05:50,489
- 你会喜欢的  - 真的
- You're gonna love it.  - Yeah.

141
00:05:50,491 --> 00:05:51,990
它是市场上评价最高的一款
It's the highest rated one on the market.

142
00:05:51,992 --> 00:05:53,325
我都不会管它叫婴儿床
I wouldn't even call it a crib.

143
00:05:53,327 --> 00:05:56,745
我会叫它宝宝专用孤独堡垒
I'd call it a Fortress of Solitude for babies.

144
00:05:56,747 --> 00:05:59,248
听上去很贵啊
Sounds expensive.

145
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:00,916
好吧 我可能是
Okay, well, I may have gone

146
00:06:00,918 --> 00:06:04,086
有点花过头了 但是安全是无价的嘛
a bit overboard, but you can't put a price on safety.

147
00:06:04,088 --> 00:06:07,506
不过假如真想标价 它后面的零比你想象的要多
Though if you did, it's more zeroes than you're expecting.

148
00:06:08,509 --> 00:06:10,092
但是这是能买到的最安全的婴儿床了
But it's the safest crib you can buy.

149
00:06:10,094 --> 00:06:12,094
而且如果你不喜欢的话 我们还可以把它退回去
And if you don't like it, we can return it.

150
00:06:12,096 --> 00:06:14,012
- 好吧  - 用我们新买的小面包车退
- Fine.  - In our new minivan.

151
00:06:14,014 --> 00:06:16,181
哎呀 午饭是什么啊?
Hey, what's for lunch?

152
00:06:16,183 --> 00:06:17,900
你买了辆小面包车?!
You bought a minivan?!

153
00:06:17,902 --> 00:06:19,935
是为了宝宝嘛 而且我也没买
It's for the baby, and I didn't buy it.

154
00:06:19,937 --> 00:06:21,353
车行把它借给了我
The dealer loaned it to me

155
00:06:21,355 --> 00:06:23,489
说我有24个小时试驾
for a 24-hour test drive.

156
00:06:23,491 --> 00:06:25,574
不过车后备箱被婴儿床磨得挺厉害的
Though we did ding up the back pretty good with the crib,

157
00:06:25,576 --> 00:06:27,276
所以你们可能要买辆小面包车了
so you might have bought a minivan.

158
00:06:28,946 --> 00:06:31,580
我可不想开那个 那也太妈妈款了
I don't want to drive that. It's such a mom car.

159
00:06:31,582 --> 00:06:33,248
可是车行的人说
The guy at the dealership said

160
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:35,250
这种车已经不再是只为妈妈专用的了
they're not just for moms anymore.

161
00:06:35,252 --> 00:06:36,285
可是讲道理
Then again,

162
00:06:36,287 --> 00:06:38,787
他也确实以为你是我老公
he did think you were my husband.

163
00:06:41,175 --> 00:06:42,958
他们在做超声波的时候都这么想
They thought it at the ultrasound.

164
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:44,843
车行这么想有问题吗?
Why not at the car dealership?

165
00:06:50,718 --> 00:06:53,302
我以前从没在桌子的这半边待过啊
Never been on this side of the table before.

166
00:06:53,304 --> 00:06:55,521
我觉得自己大权在握
I feel powerful.

167
00:06:55,523 --> 00:06:56,972
